The paper discusses designing query languages for graph structured data, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the complexity of query evaluation, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC). The study of the hierarchy of expressions and the relationship between Boolean quantifiers and nesting depth of iterated bindings suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
